TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$PAR
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
$PAR
The next three problems deal with two new functions.
$PAR
The first is called the HYPERBOLIC SINE FUNCTION and is denoted as \( sinh(x) \).
$PAR
The second is called the HYPERBOLIC COSINE FUNCTION and is denoted as \( cosh(x) \).
$PAR
These two functions are both defined using either the difference or sum of exponential functions and then dividing by 2:

\[ \sinh(x) = \frac { e^x-e^{-x} } {2} \]
\[ \cosh(x) = \frac { e^x+e^{-x} } {2} \]
EOT


